  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This technique can only be performed in the Sankatto: Shodan Dachi stance. As a full-attack action, the user throws his three held weapons, first in his primary hand, then his off-hand, and finally the one held in his teeth, hitting on his full to-hit bonus. Each attack deals normal weapon damage if it hits, plus the users' Strength bonus.<br><br>If both the first and second attack hit and deal damage, the third attack if successful provokes a Fortitude save that, on a fail, will deal an additional 3d8 damage of the appropriate type (usually slashing) and cause the target to become Fatigued, or Exhausted if he already suffers from the Fatigued condition.<br><br>The weapons return to the user at the end of fullattack action, and if he has the Quick Draw feat, can be considered ready. Abilities or actions that may prevent this, such as the Deflect talent, do so as normal.</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Requires:</b> Hikiro Renken (t), BaB +11 and Sankatto: Shodan Dachi (3)</p>\n<p><b>Material Focus:</b> The user's held weapons.</p>\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
